valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubjorgard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjorgard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 7:43:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2082.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Aspiring Shadowblade...have a look and give opinions...</span><hr size=1> I recently started a shadowblade and I really like to play the class despite some difficulties associated with it..<br><br>Now  read a lot about people praising envenom as the &quot;saviour&quot; of all rogue classes...<br><br>My idea was more a template like<br>50 Stealth 50 sword, 28 Crit and some 6 points in envenom<br><br>Or <br><br>50 stealth 50 soword 21 crit 19 Envenom<br><br>Are those feasible templates...comments, suggestions..<br><br>I think in the long run I would benefit more from a maxed weapon skill then from envenom as it seems to get resisted a lot and also I don't plan to duke  it out with meleeres toe to toe...<br>so any comments would be appreciated <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujablackhand.showPublicProfile?language=EN>J A  Blackhand</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.crewsman.homestead.com/files/Demon_Hunter.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 7:53:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2082.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re. </span><hr size=1> If you are going to take poisons to 21, you might aswell atleast take it to 22 for L Enven.  As for Sword maxed and CS low, you might want to read the Sword Style requirments.  Since with your current ideas you will be near wholely dependant upon your Sword styles at higher levels.<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>Where are my Magiks!? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubjorgard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjorgard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 8:09:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2082.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re. </span><hr size=1> Yeah I know that I will be pretty dependant on my sword styles...but from my experience and from what I hear from others all you usually ever need is the Backstab/eviscerate/Kidney Rupture combo..<br>Later you may throw in a Perf or two....so I don't see a point on speccing that high in Crit...<br>And the question is if the damage put out by poison makes up the damage I would loose when I spec lower in sword and put it into envenom instead...*ponders* <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubjorgard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjorgard</A> at: 2/8/02 8:29:03 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucroverdarogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CroverDaRogue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 9:39:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2082.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re. </span><hr size=1> 1) Do you really...deep down...realize just how far away lvl 50 is? <br>2) Why do people continue to max out a line when it just flat out is NOT needed? Stealth especially...there is NO difference from a player with 40 stealth+10 in Rps/items and a person with 50 stealth from skill points. Zip zero nada.<br><br>If you want to one shot kill people...well, anytime, you need to raise CS to at least 39 for the chain. &quot;Throwing out a perf here and there&quot; won't cut it when your perf sucks because you didnt raise your spec high enough. The difference will be a couple hundred points of damage, in the least.<br><br>Envenom is fun, but not as useful as CS. At your proposed envenom lvl of 21ish, thats about 18-25 dmg per tic for 5 tics depending on lvl.<br><br>Why 50 swd? CS is the rogues bread and butter atk styles, they do more dmg and are easier to use generally than swd styles.<br><br>I personally prefer axes, since if you use Left axe at all you get the bonus from both axes, instead of just one hand giving bonuses if you use swd/axe combo. Also, axes (2h) have a slower atk speed which means bigger opening backstabs, that much easier to one-shot pvp kill with.<br><br>I appreciate you wanting to enter the world of the Shadowblade, perhaps you might wish to consider some of your options before you start to spec though.<br><br>Sinatra Fabulous<br>44.5Sb, lover of Lurikeen women<br>Palo <p><img src="http://morganfl.tripod.com//sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/sig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubjorgard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjorgard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 10:09:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2082.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re. </span><hr size=1> Cheers for the info <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ...and boy...i DO know how far away lvl 50 is...<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>I didn't consider the +item/realm Rank bonuses..so true there's no need to fully spec in stealth.....thus freeing points to put into CS <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>I don't use Axes or dualwield combos much...it's just a matter of prefernece..I don't like axes...simple as that....I rather stick to sword even if it means sacrificing some damage potential for it..the reason why to get high sword is that I have the feeling that IF I have to duke it out with someone because a screwed backstab the high sword would deal damage more consistently over time then the poison...*shrugs*..but this is just an observation I base of PvE so far as I am only lvl 16 right now...it's more a hunch then having hard evidence on it...still learning the ropes <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>I think I'll go with the 39 CS as you suggested...that seems to be a reasonable idea..but I think I gonna drop envenom comepletely...I really don't see much use for it as of now...<br>thanks for the input so far <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubjorgard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjorgard</A> at: 2/8/02 10:13:48 am<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.